  <mainDescription>Different BMI strategies taken into consideration and being practiced related to each individual BM – “AS IS” and “TO BE”&#xD;
BM. The BMI strategies are inspired by Derek F. Abell 1980 – Business should stick to their core business, Hamel 1980 –&#xD;
business should develop their core competences, Prahalad and Hamel , Cooper 1985 – Businesses should seek product&#xD;
leadership translated to value proposition leadership, Philip Kotler 1984 – Businesses should choose among market&#xD;
leadership, differentiation or focus strategy, Michael Porter 1985 – Businesses should focus on cost leadership,&#xD;
differentiate related to competitors or do a focus strategy, Sanchez 1996 – Businesses should seek reach production of&#xD;
excellence, 2000, 2001, Chan and Mabourgne 2008 – Businesses should marginalise competitors and competitions via the blue&#xD;
ocean framework, Roberto Verganti 2011 suggests focusing on meaning and the process in which the BM is or should operate.</mainDescription>
